&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Summary&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Title: &lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Chemical Production Operator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Chicago, IL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: $26.50/hour and equity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include: Up to $750/month employer contribution toward employee medical insurance, including dependent coverage, 99% employer-paid dental and vision coverage, flexible PTO, FSA benefits, 401k, paid parental leave, long-term disability insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reports to: Manufacturing Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Company&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numat is a global leader in the field of precision chemistries. Numat’s solutions are changing the way industries around the world capture and separate hazardous chemicals that negatively impact human health and the environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numat has been at the forefront of Metal-Organic Framework (MOF) research and production for over a decade and is the first company to successfully commercialize MOFs. The company’s world-class platform integrates MOFs into existing products and processes, merging chemistry innovation with manufacturing at industrial scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through bold and transformative chemistry, Numat helps its global customers and partners make meaningful progress toward their net zero and innovation objectives. Be a part of something bigger, join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hands-on role, you will support the on-site production of Numat’s growing&amp;nbsp;commercial product lines that utilize its unique adsorbents. You will be required to perform&amp;nbsp;manufacturing tasks safely, efficiently, and in a manner consistent with Numat procedures. It will be essential to communicate information effectively and professionally to your small and nimble&amp;nbsp;internal team. Your attention to detail and willingness to change in a fast-moving environment is crucial to support the team’s mission of continuous improvement and customer satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Core hours are weekdays, 7 AM – 3 PM. The position may require work on Saturday and/or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sunday, holidays, and overtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operate and maintain manufacturing equipment to produce products safely, on time, and at target quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Example activities include batch drying operations, transferring solid and liquid chemicals, packaging equipment operation, and conducting at-line quality-assurance tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with industrial control screens to monitor and adjust continuous processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete proper process documentation as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose problems with equipment or process and, within SOP guidelines, adjust or escalate issues to the Supervisor or Maintenance team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support execution of supporting tasks that keep the business running.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate powered industrial trucks (i.e., forklift) to move materials through the facility&lt;/li&gt;
